"title": "5095: Jacob, life and character of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5095: jacob, life and character of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The grandson of Abraham and son of Isaac, who was chosen by God, despite his personal faults and shortcomings, to be the recipient of the promises made to Abraham. His name means “he grasps the heel”, an allusion to the circumstances of his birth (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:25-Gen25:26\">Ge 25:25–26</a>).</p>\n<h2>Jacob's birth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21-Gen25:26\">GEN 25:21–25:26</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jacob obtains the rights of the firstborn son</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:36\">GEN 27:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:29-Gen25:34\">GEN 25:29–25:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:1-Gen27:29\">GEN 27:1–27:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16-Heb12:17\">HEB 12:16–12:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob inherits the promises made to Abraham</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:10-Gen28:15\">GEN 28:10–28:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:5\">GEN 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:29\">GEN 27:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:3-Gen28:4\">GEN 28:3–28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:11-Gen35:13\">GEN 35:11–35:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob flees to Haran</h2>\n<h3>As the result of Esau's enmity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:41-Gen27:45\">GEN 27:41–27:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:5\">GEN 28:5</a></p>\n<h3>He encounters God at Bethel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:10-Gen28:22\">GEN 28:10–28:22</a> <em>The encounter with God at Bethel confirms that Jacob has received the promise made to Abraham, and that Jacob has accepted his role of bearer of that promise to future generations.</em></p>\n<h3>He marries Leah and Rachel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:1-Gen28:2\">GEN 28:1–28:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:16-Gen29:30\">GEN 29:16–29:30</a> <em>Jacob is deceived by Laban into marrying Leah before Rachel.</em></p>\n<h3>He accumulates wealth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:29-Gen30:43\">GEN 30:29–30:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:4-Gen31:9\">GEN 31:4–31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:14-Gen31:16\">GEN 31:14–31:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:36-Gen31:42\">GEN 31:36–31:42</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob returns to Canaan</h2>\n<h3>His flight from Haran</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:1-Gen31:3\">GEN 31:1–31:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:10-Gen31:13\">GEN 31:10–31:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:17-Gen31:24\">GEN 31:17–31:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:44-Gen31:55\">GEN 31:44–31:55</a></p>\n<h3>His encounter with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:24-Gen32:30\">GEN 32:24–32:30</a></strong> <em>The change of his name from “Jacob” (meaning “he grasps the heel”, figuratively, “he deceives”) to “Israel” (meaning “he struggles with God”) confirms Jacob as the recipient of the Abrahamic blessings.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:1-Gen35:5\">GEN 35:1–35:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:9-Gen35:15\">GEN 35:9–35:15</a></p>\n<h3>His reunion with Esau</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:1-Gen33:17\">GEN 33:1–33:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jacob's children</h2>\n<h3>His twelve sons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:22-Gen35:26\">GEN 35:22–35:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:32-Gen29:35\">GEN 29:32–29:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:3-Gen30:13\">GEN 30:3–30:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:16-Gen35:18\">GEN 35:16–35:18</a></p>\n<h3>The rape of his daughter</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:1-Gen34:2\">GEN 34:1–34:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:5\">GEN 34:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:7\">GEN 34:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:13-Gen34:31\">GEN 34:13–34:31</a></p>\n<h3>His favouritism towards Joseph and Benjamin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3-Gen37:4\">GEN 37:3–37:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:31-Gen37:35\">GEN 37:31–37:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:1-Gen42:4\">GEN 42:1–42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:20\">GEN 44:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:22\">GEN 44:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:27-Gen44:31\">GEN 44:27–44:31</a></p>\n<h3>His reunion with Joseph</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:29-Gen46:30\">GEN 46:29–46:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:27-Gen45:28\">GEN 45:27–45:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:1-Gen46:4\">GEN 46:1–46:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:11\">GEN 47:11</a></p>\n<h3>Jacob blesses his descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:21\">HEB 11:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:15-Gen48:20\">GEN 48:15–48:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:1-Gen49:28\">GEN 49:1–49:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob's death and burial</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:28-Gen47:30\">GEN 47:28–47:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:29-Gen49:33\">GEN 49:29–49:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:2-Gen50:3\">GEN 50:2–50:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:12-Gen50:13\">GEN 50:12–50:13</a></p>",
